50|$|Abdul Wahhab {{joined the}} <b>Tabligh</b> Jamaat {{during the life}} of its founder, Muhammad Ilyas Kandhlawi. He arrived at Nizamuddin markaz on the 1st of January 1944. He got the sohbah of Maulana Ilyas for six months. He left his job to devote his {{time and effort to}} the Jamaat, {{and he was one of}} the first five people in Pakistan who offered their entire life for doing <b>Tabligh</b> work. He was a direct {{companion}} of Maulana Muhammad Ilyas Kandhlawi, Yusuf Kandhlawi, and Inamul Hasan Kandhlawi.|$|E
